item.title: Coronavirus death toll soars past 560
Report that said virus can spread before symptoms was flawed
Passengers test positive for coronavirus on cruise ship
item.description: Thousands of passengers and crew members on the Diamond Princess cruise ship are being held on board after 10 passengers tested positive for the Wuhan coronavirus.

item.title: Trump acquitted by Senate, bringing a bitter and historic impeachment to a close
item.description: The Senate voted to acquit President Donald Trump on two articles of impeachment Wednesday, marking the inevitable and historic end to a bitterly fought, divisive impeachment trial that will reverberate into the 2020 election and shape Trump's presidential legacy.

item.title: Romney breaks with Republicans and votes to remove Trump
Watch Romney's powerful speech on Senate floor
item.description: Sen. Mitt Romney (R-UT) explained to the Senate why he plans to vote to convict President Trump on both counts in the Senate impeachment trial, calling Trump's actions "an appalling abuse of public trust."

item.title: Kirk Douglas, legendary Hollywood star, dies at 103
item.description: Kirk Douglas, one of the great Hollywood leading men whose off-screen life was nearly as colorful as his on-screen exploits, has died, according to his son, actor Michael Douglas. He was 103.

item.title: These 2 Nancy Pelosi photos perfectly sum up the state of the union
Nancy Pelosi calls Trump's SOTU a 'manifesto of mistruths'
item.description: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi called President Donald Trump's State of the Union address a "manifesto of mistruths" after appearing to rip up a copy of his speech as the event ended.

item.title: Plane breaks apart after skidding off runway
item.description: An airplane skidded off the runway and broke apart while landing at Istanbul's Sabiha Gokcen airport, according to CNN Turk.

item.title: Buttigieg still leads as Iowa keeps counting
item.description: The Democratic presidential race has shifted to New Hampshire, with the full field of 2020 contenders blanketing the state ahead of its Tuesday primary.

item.title: Avalanche kills rescuers searching for survivors of previous avalanche
item.description: At least 31 people, many of them rescuers, have been killed and dozens are feared trapped after two avalanches near Turkey's eastern border with Iran, authorities say.

item.title: Penguins' speech patterns similar to humans, study finds
item.description: In most human languages, the most frequently used words are short. Think "the," and, "of " and "a."

item.title: Lesotho's First Lady charged with murdering husband's ex-wife
item.description: The First Lady of Lesotho, Maesaiah Thabane has been charged with murdering her husband's ex-wife in a crime that has gripped the tiny mountainous kingdom.

item.title: Charges will be dropped against a surgeon and his girlfriend accused of raping women, prosecutor says
item.description: Prosecutors in California plan to drop charges against a surgeon and his girlfriend who were accused of drugging and raping women, Orange County District Attorney Todd Spitzer said Tuesday.

item.title: Warren's answer about male candidates' odds draws laughter
item.description: During a town hall in New Hampshire, Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren answered if she believes male candidates have a better chance of beating President Trump in 2020 solely based on their gender.

item.title: A critic of the Chechen leader was murdered in a French hotel room
item.description: French police are investigating the murder of a Chechen blogger, who was a vocal critic of President Ramzan Kadyrov, in a hotel room in Lille.

item.title: Astronaut Christina Koch spent a record-breaking 328 days in space. Here's what she did
item.description: NASA astronaut Christina Koch made the most of her first trip to the International Space Station by breaking the record for the longest single spaceflight by a woman and conducting the first all-female spacewalk with fellow NASA astronaut Jessica Meir.

item.title: Animal rights group ends naked anti-fur campaign
item.description: The "I'd rather go naked than wear fur" campaign of animal rights charity PETA has ended after nearly 30 years. The ads featured celebrities stripping off to protest fur.

item.title: Where to eat in New York, according to its top models
item.description: For models, there's more to fashion week than walking a runway or two. Days start in the early hours, with multiple castings, fittings and shows to cram into 24 hours; naturally, they need to keep well fueled. CNN asked four models where they like to eat in New York during fashion week, as well as how they spend their spare time in the city -- if they have any.

item.title: The California firefighters who volunteered to battle flames in Australia return home
item.description: Capt. Leonard Dimaculangan hugged his daughter for the first time in a month after battling flames half way across the world in Australia.

item.title: Madonna offers to rent her apartment to Harry and Meghan
item.description: Madonna offered to sublet her New York apartment to The Duke and Duchess of Sussex in an Instagram video.

item.title: Trolls attacks this lawmaker's outfit. She shut them down with a single tweet
item.description: A British lawmaker has struck back against online trolls who criticized her for baring her shoulder in Parliament.

item.title: Finland will equalize its family-leave policy, giving each parent 164 days of leave after birth
item.description: Finland is switching up its parental leave laws, and this time, the government says they're putting children at the center.

item.title: 'Rubik Mona Lisa' could sell for $166,000
item.description: An artist's interpretation of Leonardo da Vinci's "Mona Lisa" -- fashioned out of hundreds of Rubik's cubes -- is expected to go under the hammer at a Paris auction later this month.

item.title: Cosmopolitan Magazine cancels its 'Bachelor' digital cover, after contestant modeled a 'White Lives Matter' slogan
item.description: Cosmopolitan Magazine is nixing its planned "The Bachelor" cover, after learning the contestant selected previously modeled clothing with the slogan "White Lives Matter."

item.title: Palestinians say Trump's deal is racist. But their leaders don't know how to fight it
item.description: A gloomy winter of Palestinian discontent has been made grimmer still by Donald Trump's new "peace plan." It's been presented as a "take-it-or-leave it" offer, and invited comparisons with apartheid from its critics.

item.title: World's oldest wooden structure unearths new Neolithic skills
item.description: Archaeologists have uncovered the oldest wooden structure ever found. They believe the water well was built around 5256 B.C. by farmers.

item.title: A kayaker vanished last month in the Everglades. Days later, his phone washed ashore with clues
item.description: A Virginia kayaker who vanished during a solo trip in the Florida Everglades has been found after his cell phone washed ashore and authorities used it to recover data on his location.

item.title: Ex-PM's bodyguard left loaded gun in plane bathroom, reports say
item.description: David Cameron's police bodyguard is under investigation after reports emerged that he left a loaded handgun and the former British Prime Minister's passport in the toilet on a commercial flight.

item.title: School meeting about racism ends with racist remark
item.description: A community meeting, meant to promote diversity at Saline Area Schools in Michigan, ended in tension after a parent yelled out racist comments.

item.title: Jay-Z explains sitting during National Anthem at Super Bowl LIV
item.description: Jay-Z has a message for all those who believed he and his wife Beyoncé were engaging in a silent protest at this year's Super Bowl: "It actually wasn't. Sorry."

item.title: PETA ends 'I'd Rather Go Naked' anti-fur campaign after three decades
item.description: The phrase "I'd rather go naked than wear fur" has been credited to celebrities -- in various states of undress -- from Pamela Anderson to Eva Mendes, Pink and Dennis Rodman.

item.title: Airline helps out boy who lost teddy bear on plane
item.description: A young boy was gifted a new teddy bear from Southwest Airlines after he lost his old one on a flight.

item.title: Closed Japanese McDonald's gets tongue-in-cheek sendoff from rival Burger King
item.description: As a McDonald's in Tokyo's Akihabara neighborhood closed down after 22 years in business and posted a thank-you poster outside its store, its arch competitor Burger King responded with a seemingly compassionate adieu.

item.title: Dead monster galaxy found lurking in the distant universe
item.description: An ultramassive monster galaxy dating back to the early days of the universe lived fast and died young, astronomers say in a new study.

item.title: Yarn made from human skin could soon be stitching up your wounds
item.description: It may sound like a gruesome detail from a dystopian movie, but a team of scientists believe yarn grown from human skin could soon be used to stitch up surgical patients and repair organs.

item.title: Dentist suspended after patient dies and 14 others suffer heart infections
item.description: A New Jersey oral surgeon has agreed to a five-year license suspension and nearly $300,000 in penalties after one of his patients died and 14 others suffered serious heart infections, according to Monday's press release from the NJ Division of Consumer Affairs.

item.title: Two stars fight, and the image is stunning
item.description: Stars that have companions aren't always friendly to them, as evidenced by a stellar confrontation witnessed by astronomers.

item.title: What the airport of the future will look like
item.description: Whether it's biometrics to get through security, an airline app that tells you if your flight is delayed or free Wi-Fi and charging areas for all travelers, there's no doubt technology this past decade has helped enhance the airport experience for fliers around the world.

item.title: Sand dunes can 'communicate' with each other
item.description: Sand dunes can communicate with their neighbors and let them know they need space, according to research published by scientists at Cambridge University.

item.title: Barcelona in crisis after Messi lashes out at club's hierarchy
item.description: Barcelona is in crisis after captain Lionel Messi lashed out at the club's sporting director Eric Abidal for accusing the players of not working hard enough under Ernesto Valverde.

item.title: Cats, shoes, Kardashians -- how fashion embraced the meme
item.description: The fashion industry -- with its close relationship to celebrity and pop culture -- finds itself at home in the world of online memes.

item.title: World's most powerful passport gets a makeover
item.description: The world's most powerful passport just got a makeover.

item.title: 'It's urban, but it's beautiful': NYC through the eyes of its favorite photographer
item.description: For photographer Landon Nordeman, finding beauty in the everyday is a full-time job. So, it's no surprise that his hometown of New York provides an endless source of creative and personal inspiration.

item.title: Singer reacts to ex-wife Jessica Simpson's new book
item.description: Nick Lachey spoke about his ex-wife Jessica Simpson's new memoir, "Open Book," during an interview on NBC's "Today."

item.title: What happened in this abandoned village?
item.description: The village of Al Madam is being gradually reclaimed by the desert.

item.title: With travelers unable to visit, China's museums are moving exhibitions online
item.description: Chinese travelers can't visit their country's museums right now. So the museums are bringing the exhibits to them -- virtually.

item.title: China reports almost 3,700 new cases in a day | 20 cases confirmed on a cruise ship in Japan
Death toll spikes again as outbreak shows no signs of slowing
item.description: The death toll and number of people infected by the Wuhan coronavirus continues to grow, with no signs of slowing despite severe quarantine and population control methods put in place in central China.
